reviewContent: I get to work with all kinds of new technology as a security instructor so I'm not easily impressed by much. When I ordered two of the R3 smart rings, I bought them in the largest size possible so my students could see each and every detail of the rings. To my surprise, the ring hides it's capabilities very well. When I showed the rings to some of my students over the weekend, they all said "Nice ring but so what." Once I told them that I could open doors with it, pass information using my phone, pay for items, and communicate with other devices, they thought I was nuts. Each ring is stunning in appearance and shows no outward clues of what it really is, which is a NFC computer and an ID card along with other healthy FIR gems and magnetic properties. I'm used to working with very small chips and now computers that are the size of a nail-head but these rings are functional jewelry computers. No power required! They are amazing to work with and exciting to show to curious minds.
